[[{"text": ["You really don't want to change what python points to, because some programs might expect Python 2, and break."], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "python", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 0, "childList": []}]}, {"text": ["The solution is to use virtualenv: create an isolated Python 3 environment (with the -p python3 option), activate it, and you're good to go."], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": [{"text": "virtualenv", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://pypi.python.org/pypi/virtualenv"}, {"text": "-p python3", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "childList": []}]}], [{"text": ["Since you have Linux, and if you want to simply type \"python\" instead of \"python3\" in order to run Python programs, a solution is simply to define an alias in you shell configuration file (.bashrc, etc.).", "For Bourne shells, it should be something like"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n alias python=python3\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 1}, {"text": ["(or whatever your Python 3 name is)."], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 2, "childList": []}, {"text": ["This way, you do not have to change anything on your system, so this solution should quite innocuous and it should not break your system."], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 3, "childList": []}], [{"text": ["It is not advisable."], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": []}, {"text": ["You could write at the top in your own script (a shebang):"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n #!/usr/bin/env python3\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 2}, {"text": ["If you're on Windows then install pylauncher.", "It understands #!."], "childNum": 3, "tag": "p", "senID": 3, "childList": [{"text": "pylauncher", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [{"text": "pylauncher", "tag": "code"}], "childNum": 1, "href": "https://bitbucket.org/vinay.sajip/pylauncher/downloads"}, {"text": "pylauncher", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": -1, "childList": []}, {"text": "#!", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 1, "childList": []}]}, {"text": ["On Linux to make your script executable, run once:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 4, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n $ chmod +x your-script\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 5}, {"text": ["After that, to run your script:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 6, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n $ ./your-script\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 7}, {"text": ["For interactive use you could create virtualenv as @Petr Viktorin points out.", "To install/upgrade (versions from Ubuntu's repositries are too old):"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 8, "childList": [{"text": "@Petr Viktorin", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://stackoverflow.com/questions/7679674/changing-default-python-to-another-version/7679735#7679735"}]}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n $ pip install -U virtualenv{,wrapper}\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 9}, {"text": ["Follow instructions in /path/to/virtualenvwrapper.sh, to create virtualenv that uses python3:"], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 10, "childList": [{"text": "/path/to/virtualenvwrapper.sh", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 0, "childList": []}, {"text": "python3", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "childList": []}]}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n $ mkvirtualenv --python python3 py3\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 11}, {"text": ["To activate virtualenv:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 12, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n $ workon py3\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 13}, {"text": ["In an active virtualenv python refers to /path/virtualenv/bin/python.", "So you could run:"], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 14, "childList": [{"text": "python", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 0, "childList": []}, {"text": "/path/virtualenv/bin/python", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": -1, "childList": []}]}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n $ python your_module.py\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 15}], [{"text": ["On Linux/Mac OS you can use python3 instead of python."], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "python3", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 0, "childList": []}, {"text": "python", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "childList": []}]}], [{"text": ["You could follow this procedure:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": []}, {"text": ["sudo rm /usr/bin/python"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": [{"text": "sudo rm /usr/bin/python", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 0, "childList": []}]}, {"text": ["sudo ln -s /usr/bin/python3.1 /usr/bin/python"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 2, "childList": [{"text": "sudo ln -s /usr/bin/python3.1 /usr/bin/python", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 0, "childList": []}]}, {"text": ["But as already stated by Petr Viktorin, any programs that would expect python v2 would stop to work.", "So use with caution.", "You can undo the change by running:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 3, "childList": []}, {"text": ["sudo rm /usr/bin/python"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 4, "childList": [{"text": "sudo rm /usr/bin/python", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 0, "childList": []}]}, {"text": ["sudo ln -s /usr/bin/python2.6 /usr/bin/python"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 5, "childList": [{"text": "sudo ln -s /usr/bin/python2.6 /usr/bin/python", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 0, "childList": []}]}], [{"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n unlink /usr/bin/python\nln -s /usr/bin/python3.1 /usr/bin/python\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 0}], [{"text": ["Try update-alternatives for Linux."], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "update-alternatives", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://linux.die.net/man/8/update-alternatives"}]}]]